{"_links":{"self":{"href":"/api/v2/datasets/doi%3A10.5061%2Fdryad.gqnk98smc"},"stash:versions":{"href":"/api/v2/datasets/doi%3A10.5061%2Fdryad.gqnk98smc/versions"},"stash:version":{"href":"/api/v2/versions/117186"},"stash:download":{"href":"/api/v2/datasets/doi%3A10.5061%2Fdryad.gqnk98smc/download"},"curies":[{"name":"stash","href":"https://github.com/datadryad/dryad-app/blob/main/documentation/apis/link_relations.md#{rel}","templated":"true"}]},"identifier":"doi:10.5061/dryad.gqnk98smc","id":61938,"storageSize":1060745,"relatedPublicationISSN":"2046-1402","title":"Demographic data, reporting guidelines underlying the manuscript: The effect of morning versus evening administration of Empagliflozin on its pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics characteristics in healthy adults: a two way cross over, non-randomized trial","authors":[{"firstName":"Rana","lastName":"ElDash","email":"ranaeldash711@gmail.com","affiliation":"Heliopolis University","affiliationROR":"https://ror.org/02tme6r37","affiliations":[{"name":"Heliopolis University","ror_id":"https://ror.org/02tme6r37"}],"orcid":"0000-0001-6605-2549"},{"firstName":"Sara","lastName":"Shaheen","email":"drsara61181@gmail.com","affiliation":"AinShms University","affiliations":[{"name":"AinShms University"}]},{"firstName":"Nagwa","lastName":"Sabri","email":"nagwa.sabri@yahoo.com","affiliation":"AinShms University","affiliations":[{"name":"AinShms University"}]}],"abstract":"\u003cp style=\"text-align:start;text-indent:0px;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-style:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"white-space:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cb\u003eBackground\u003c/b\u003e: Empagliflozin is an SGLT2 inhibitor approved for use in patients with Diabetes Mellitus type 2 (DMT2) with- or without other cardiovascular disease. Empagliflozin is taken once daily without rationale on the optimal timing for administration. This study aimed\u003cb\u003e \u003c/b\u003eto determine the chronopharmacological effects of morning vs evening administration of empagliflozin 10 mg in Healthy Egyptian adults, by investigating the pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics parameters of empagliflozin depending on the intake time. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:start;text-indent:0px;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-style:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"white-space:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cb\u003eMethods: \u003c/b\u003eAn \u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003eopen label, sequential\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e, two‐way crossover trial comprised two periods with a washout period of 7 days\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e. Pharmacokinetics parameters (T\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003csub\u003emax\u003c/sub\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e (h), C\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003csub\u003emax\u003c/sub\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e (ng/ml), AUC \u003csub\u003e0-t\u003c/sub\u003e (ng.h/ml)) as primary endpoints, and (AUC \u003csub\u003e0 to ∞\u003c/sub\u003e(ng.h/ml)) as secondary endpoint were assessed. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003eMethod validation was done prior to injection in LC/MS/MS and samples were processed by Liquid-Liquid extraction. The pharmacodynamic profile (UGE \u003csub\u003e0-24\u003c/sub\u003e) was determined after method validation (glucose hexokinase method).\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:start;text-indent:0px;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-style:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"white-space:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cb\u003eResults: \u003c/b\u003eT\u003csub\u003emax\u003c/sub\u003e increased by (35%) in the evening phase compared to the morning phase, while C\u003csub\u003emax\u003c/sub\u003e decreased by (-6.5%)in the evening dose compared to the morning dose. Besides, AUC\u003csub\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e0 to ∞\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/sub\u003e increased in the evening phase by (8.25%) compared to the morning phase. The mean cumulative amount of glucose excreted; UGE (\u003csub\u003e0-24\u003c/sub\u003e) increased by (43%) in the evening dose compared to the morning dose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp style=\"text-align:start;text-indent:0px;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-style:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-weight:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"letter-spacing:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"white-space:normal;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cb\u003eConclusion\u003c/b\u003e:\u003cb\u003e \u003c/b\u003eDespite the difference in pharmacokinetics parameters between evening and morning doses, C\u003csub\u003emax\u003c/sub\u003e, AUC\u003csub\u003e0-t\u003c/sub\u003e, AUC\u003csub\u003e0-∞\u003c/sub\u003e, didn’t differ on the bioequivalence level. In addition, as UGE\u003csub\u003e(0-24)\u003c/sub\u003e didn’t statistically differ, thus, we can conclude that there is no statistical significance between the morning and evening doses.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n","keywords":["adult demography","diabetes ","Pharmacodynamics","reporting guidelines"],"methods":"\u003cp\u003eDemographic data were collected by taking participants' data, in addition to, blood tests to measure fasting blood sugar, triglycerides, high and low denisty lipo protein.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n","relatedWorks":[{"relationship":"dataset","identifierType":"DOI","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.brv15dv8j"},{"relationship":"dataset","identifierType":"DOI","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.7h44j0zt1"},{"relationship":"dataset","identifierType":"DOI","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.k0p2ngf7b"},{"relationship":"primary_article","identifierType":"DOI","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.12688/f1000research.51114.1"}],"versionNumber":13,"versionStatus":"submitted","curationStatus":"Published","versionChanges":"metadata_changed","publicationDate":"2021-04-28","lastModificationDate":"2021-04-28","visibility":"public","sharingLink":"http://datadryad.org/dataset/doi:10.5061/dryad.gqnk98smc","changedFields":["related_identifiers",[{"index":3,"id":"https://doi.org/10.12688/f1000research.51114.1","type":"primary_article","relation":"iscitedby"}]],"license":"https://spdx.org/licenses/CC0-1.0.html","metrics":{"views":217,"downloads":32,"citations":4}}